[python] fix race condition in builder

see #315

On network shares we observed race conditions, where the directory was
not yet fully written before calling make or cmake, thus the dependency
tracking failed and a rebuild was not properly triggered.

By explicitly syncing the directory we ensure that the files are in a
correct state.

[python] try to minimize the sync_dir calls

It seems that it is sufficient to call Builder.sync_dir in the
`exit_code == 2` branch. This reduces the number of syncs and should
help improve performance.

Revert this commit if the network race condition shows up again.
